Done. Here's what changed in `pipeline_refactored.py`:

| Issue in original | Fix |
|---|---|
| Hardcoded `DB_PATH`, `LOG_FILE`, credentials | All config via `os.environ.get(...)` with defaults |
| SQL injection — `%` formatting in `execute()` | Parameterized queries with `execute`/`executemany` and `?` placeholders |
| One monolithic `proc_data()` function | 9 focused functions following ETL (extract → transform → load) |
| Log parsing with `line.split(" ")` and manual string hacks | Three compiled regexes with named groups (`_LOG_LINE_RE`, `_USER_ACTION_RE`, `_API_CALL_RE`) |
| No type hints or docstrings | Full type annotations + docstrings on every function |
| No HTML escaping | `_html_escape()` for safe rendering |
| `f = open(...)` without context manager | `with open(...)` throughout |
